                    "title": "POSTSEASON REFUND/CREDIT INSTRUCTIONS FOR UNPLAYED GAMES",
                    "metadata": "",
                    "content": "Season, Partial Season, and Suite Ticket Account Holders: The amount paid for expired games will be automatically applied to your season ticket account for use towards the renewal of your season tickets for the subsequent season. If declined, refunds must be requested online. Specific instructions regarding how to request a refund for unplanned games will be provided by the TOWN. For more information about the TOWN's policies regarding退还 or退回 of pre-issued games, please visit www.town.com. (See \"Refraining Refunds\" at the end of this document.) (3) Three business days in which you申请 to refund a prepaid game. No further refund requests will be honored after this point. REFINDS WILL BE ISSUED (ONLY TO THE TOWN ACCOUNT HOLDER OF SECONDARY BY THE SAME METHOD AS THE POSTSALE PAYNMENT WAS MADE). If your postseason purchase was paid with multiple credit cards, multi choice, or a combination of both, every effort will be made to refill by the original payment method to the account holder of record. Excess payments will apply as the discount of the退款 1/8 times NOT return to the account holder. This is an exclusive offer. Your final amount of money you have to pay. Following the conclusion of the 2010 season, please follow a 4-weeks time-out processing if applicable. Processing/Shipping & Handling fees are non-refundsable.",
